            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "CHSEP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Chemical yields were determined gravimetrically",
                "for silver chloride. Otherwise the 1.3-Yr Cd-109 in the",
                "cadmium carrier was used as internal monitor for yield",
                "determinations. A 12 mg/cm**2 aluminium foils was used",
                "to absorb the conversion electrons from Cd-109 when",
                " 2.3-days Cd-115-G and 43-days Cd-115-M were beta",
                "counted. The Recovered amount of Cd-109 was determined",
                "either by counting of the 88-keV gamma peak or by beta",
                "counting with the aluminium foil removed [after the",
                "cadmium activity had decayed for 8-10 months]."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Beam intensity of Stockholm Institute was 50",
                "muA, approximately.  Beam intensity at Karlsruhe was",
                "1-4 muA. The standard irradiation time was 10 min, but",
                "2 min and 30 min were also performed."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "To determine the yield ratio of the cadmium isomers,",
                "these were separated from 21-min Ag-115 after a",
                "complete decay of other short lived precursors.  Since,",
                "however, the time used for separation is somewhat less",
                "than the half-Live of 21-min Ag-115 appropriate",
                "corrections are determined by measuring the amounts of",
                "cadmium grown from isolated 21-min Ag-115."
              ]
            }
          ],
